subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen
(
Fig. 1 E
). Subshiny, dark brown with medium portion of tergites and sternites light brown; setae sparse, thin, and more elongate on lateral margin. Male terminalia (
Fig. 2
): Segment 6 with bilobed ventral margin (
Fig. 2 C
). Epandrium with oval margin around the anus. Bacilliform sclerites elongated, free from each other and connected to the hypandrium, inverted U-shaped (
Fig. 2 E
). Surstylus robust, geniculate, median portion with projection on inner side and a small protuberance on dorsal surface (
Figs. 2 E, F
), flattened laterally with an acuminate apex directed to dorsal surface (
Fig. 2 D
) and covered by robust setae on apical half. Cerci fused to each other and to epandrium, triangular, narrow, longer than wide and with several elongate setae (
Figs. 2 E, F
). Ventral plate of hypandrium with apical margin slightly trilobed (
Fig 2 G
). Phallus obovate, wide with rounded apex (
Figs. 2 G, I
). Ejaculatory apodeme club-shaped with rough apical half (
Figs. 2 G, H, I
).
